            <fieldset id='encodings'>
                <legend class="text-secondary">Encodings</legend>
                BEAR: the BEAR encoding represents each position of an RNA molecule with a character taken from a set of
                83, each describing its structural context and its length (Mattei et al., 2014).<br>
                quickBEAR(qBEAR): qBEAR was originally developed as a way to show alignments of RNA structures in a Logo
                form (Crooks et al., 2004), where each position of an RNA molecule is described by one of 18 characters
                encoding for structural contexts and length groups (Pietrosanto et al., 2016).<br>
                The following TABLE illustrates the mapping between Secondary Structure Elements and qBEAR and BEAR
                encodings used throughout the work. Motivations for BEAR can be found in the original work (Mattei et
                al., 2014).<br>
